Introduction

Kyuu is a hip-hop artist from South Korea who made his debut in February 2018 with the single "Come Over." He continued to build his career with tracks like "Come Over" and "I Need Selfish Time." Later that year, Kyuu released his first EP, ROMANCEISCOMMON, an introspective project capturing fleeting, memorable moments.

Following this, he introduced his second EP, CHILLINGISRARE, and, in 2020, his first full-length album, ALLFORNOTHING. Around this time, he transitioned his stage name from Nunsseop to kyuu, marking a new phase in his artistic journey.
